Barclays, Cairn, LSE, Xstrata: U.K., Irish Equity Market Preview

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t   a n d   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-04-05T06:42:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/lse-group-mouchel-xstrata-u-k-irish-equity-market-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
that may have unusual share-price changes in U.K. and Irish
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last market close.  The benchmark  FTSE 100 Index (UKX)  gained 7.06 points, or 0.1
percent, to 6,016.98. The  FTSE All-Share Index (ASX)  rose 0.2 percent
while Ireland’s ISEQ Index advanced 0.4 percent.  Amlin Plc (AML)  : The insurer said claims arising from
the earthquake and tsunami in  Japan , the earthquake in  New
Zealand  and the floods in Australia may total as much as 275
million pounds ($443 million). The stock slid 0.2 percent to
386.7 pence.  Bank of Ireland Plc (BKIR ID): The country’s largest bank
hired Deutsche Bank AG to sell an almost 3 billion-euro ($4.3
billion) portion of its project finance business. The shares
jumped 9.3 percent to 34 euro cents in Dublin.  Barclays Plc (BARC)  : Chief Executive Officer Robert Diamond is weighing increasing the firm’s risk profile amid
expectations at the bank that a profit measure will decline or
remain flat this year, the Financial Times reported, citing
people familiar with the matter. The shares fell 0.4 percent to
288.3 pence.  BP Plc (BP/)  :  Europe ’s second-largest oil company has
applied to drill one well in the deep waters of the  Gulf of
Mexico  since an exploration ban was lifted in October, according
to a person in the U.S. government who asked not to be named
because a decision hasn’t been reached. The shares retreated 0.2
percent to 469.25 pence.  Cairn Energy Plc (CNE)  : India’s capital markets
regulator approved an open offer by Sesa Goa Ltd., a unit of
 Vedanta Resources Plc (VED)  , for shares of Cairn India Ltd.
as part of a $9.6 billion acquisition plan, Vedanta Chairman
Anil Agarwal said in Mumbai. Cairn fell 0.3 percent to 462.2
pence while Vedanta was little changed at 2,412 pence.  Drax Group Plc (DRX)  : The utility said it reached an
agreement with HM Revenue & Customs over its Eurobond financing
that will result in the release of 180 million pounds cash tax
relief. The shares rallied 2 percent to 415.3 pence.  HMV Group Plc (HMV)  : The music retailer said today
trading conditions have remained difficult and it now expects
profit before tax and exceptional items for the full year to be
around 30 million pounds. The shares were unchanged at 15.25
pence.  London Stock Exchange Group Plc (LSE)  : TMX Group Inc. (X
CN) and LSE will apply for Canadian regulatory approval of their
C$3.2 billion ($3.3 billion) combination “in weeks,” TMX Chief
Executive Officer Thomas Kloet said. LSE shares gained 0.2
percent to 857.5 pence.  Mouchel Group Plc (MCHL)  : The U.K. roadbuilder said it’s
no longer in discussions with any party regarding a potential
offer for the company. The shares dropped 12 percent to 81.75
pence.  Xstrata Plc (XTA)  : The mining company with operations in
19 countries may increase coal output by about 80 percent within
five years to meet rising demand, Nomura Holdings Inc. said. The
stock advanced 1.6 percent to 1,511 pence.  To contact the reporters on this story:
